snippet.title: ✅  Jeremy Clarkson: TV star's X-rated Amber Heard confession before 'boring Johnny Depp case'
snippet.description:

✍ Sign up for FREE now and never miss the top Royal stories again.  SUBSCRIBE  Invalid email We will use your email address only for sending you newsletters. Please see our Privacy Notice for details of your data protection rights. Jeremy Clarkson hit the headlines for branding Amber Heard and Johnny Depp’s battle in London High Court “boring” this week. This isn’t the first time the TV star has come under fire for his response to the US actress. When she appeared on ‘Top Gear’, he was deemed to have made a number of X-rated remarks and “ogled” at the star.   Trending    The controversial host, who left the BBC show in 2015 after an altercation with a producer, made inappropriate comments when Amber appeared to promote her film ‘Drive Angry’. She joined a roster of celebrities to try to get the fastest lap time in a “reasonably priced car” back in 2011. During a cringeworthy interview with Jeremy in Series 16 Episode 5, he was reported to have told the actress: “I’m picturing you naked.” ...
